The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has arrested Nigerian musician, Naira Marley, real name Afeez Fashola. The upcoming singer is currently being questioned at the EFFC office in Lagos over issues relating to internet fraud, also known as Yahoo-Yahoo. This has already sparked a lot of reactions on social media. The singer has in the past days used his social media platform to validate the act as well. He also recently released a song called ‘Am I a Yahoo boy?’ with fellow artist Zlatan Ibile. See reactions below: